techmeme.title: Peter Naylor, Netflix VP of ad sales since August 2022, is leaving, and the company will hire a head of US and Canada ad sales to fill his spot (Caitlin Huston/The Hollywood Reporter)
Sources: OpenAI has talked to chip designers including Broadcom about developing an AI server chip and hired former members of a Google unit that produces TPUs (The Information)
Netflix reports Q2 revenue up 16.8% YoY to $9.56B, vs. $9.53B est., paid memberships up 16.5% YoY to 277.65M, vs. 274.4M est., net income up 44% YoY to $2.15B (Lillian Rizzo/CNBC)
Docs: Canadian PE firm PartnerOne paid $28.2M for HeadSpin, whose 2023 revenue was $21M and its Q1 2024 was $5M; HeadSpin was valued at $1.1B in 2020 (Marina Temkin/TechCrunch)
Austin-based Thoughtful AI, which provides healthcare revenue collection tools, raised a $20M Series A led by Drive Capital, bringing its total funding to $35M (Mike Wheatley/SiliconANGLE)
